  "text": "Algorithms MLS and MLSM. Algorithm MLS (Maximal Label Search) generalizes the well-known algorithms MCS from [CITATION_1] , LexBFS from [CITATION_2] , LexDFS and MNS from [CITATION_3] . Algorithm MLS has a graph G and a labeling structure L as input and an ordering of G as output. It can be seen as a generic algorithm with parameter L whose instances are the algorithms L-MLS for each labeling structure L, having a graph G as input and an ordering of G as output. In the following definitions, N + denotes the set of positive integers.",
